WEBVTT

00:15.980 --> 00:17.690
I missed you a lot.

00:24.800 --> 00:30.320
I couldn't keep you out of my head.

00:32.119 --> 00:33.550
I kept myself busy,

00:34.230 --> 00:35.570
tried to distract myself

00:36.210 --> 00:38.110
and drank a lot.

00:41.630 --> 00:44.100
But I still missed you a lot.

00:56.000 --> 00:57.760
You didn't expect this?

01:01.250 --> 01:02.800
Think about it.

01:04.120 --> 01:06.470
I meant everything I said.

01:21.630 --> 01:22.590
Get some rest.

01:24.030 --> 01:25.830
I was going to take you back

01:26.210 --> 01:28.860
but I'm running late. I have to go now.

01:31.070 --> 01:32.990
I need to report to headquarters.

01:35.940 --> 01:37.740
Can I use the phone in headquarters?

01:39.360 --> 01:41.720
I need to contact someone.

01:46.340 --> 01:49.340
Jacinto Unit! Report damages at the current time.

01:50.770 --> 01:51.960
3 missing,

01:51.960 --> 01:54.020
20 dead, and 42 injured.

01:54.020 --> 01:56.200
Nothing further, sir!

02:16.310 --> 02:17.880
Communication lines to the Mouru Unit were cut?

02:18.990 --> 02:20.100
Yes.

02:20.100 --> 02:21.430
How long will it take to fix it?

02:21.430 --> 02:24.230
We're working on it, but it'll take a couple of days.

02:25.630 --> 02:27.340
The meeting starts in five minutes.

02:35.590 --> 02:37.370
I was with him

02:38.220 --> 02:40.360
at his last moments.

02:42.610 --> 02:49.760
He asked me to deliver this message to you.

02:51.660 --> 02:54.780
I'm lying here looking at the sky without working.

02:54.780 --> 02:56.460
This is nice.

02:57.390 --> 03:00.090
This is my lucky day.

03:01.770 --> 03:05.890
My children have already finished university.

03:06.320 --> 03:09.090
They can take care of themselves.

03:09.630 --> 03:10.930
My wife...

03:17.450 --> 03:23.240
My wife... we had more days of looking at

03:23.240 --> 03:26.090
each other's pictures than living together.

03:28.390 --> 03:31.030
She's going to look at my picture

03:31.030 --> 03:33.480
for the rest of her life.

03:39.510 --> 03:42.560
You'll receive a pension from the company

03:43.630 --> 03:46.630
and his nephew will take care of everything.

03:49.290 --> 03:50.560
Yes.

03:52.100 --> 04:03.070
And... He told you not to be single for too long.

04:30.280 --> 04:31.940
The emergency operations are over.

04:32.960 --> 04:35.020
Thank you, Dr. Song.

04:42.900 --> 04:44.080
It looks like a wedding ring, doesn't it?

04:44.080 --> 04:45.000
Yes.

04:46.130 --> 04:47.640
Did you steal it?

04:52.720 --> 04:54.630
It belongs to a patient just finished his operation,

04:56.770 --> 04:58.770
but I can't give it back to him.

05:26.310 --> 05:27.930
Until you get rid of your cast,

05:27.930 --> 05:29.180
keep it like this.

05:31.060 --> 05:32.280
Thank you.

05:39.790 --> 05:41.010
You can't do this to me.

05:41.510 --> 05:42.710
You have to do this.

05:42.710 --> 05:44.790
They donated blood so that they could interview you.

05:45.130 --> 05:46.900
I’ve already drawn blood from him. What should I do?

05:48.280 --> 05:50.580
Exactly. Now what can they do.

05:51.290 --> 05:52.570
To the right!

05:52.720 --> 05:54.310
Can you help me?

05:54.310 --> 05:55.920
Aren't you hungry?

05:55.920 --> 05:57.530
Let's finish this up and eat.

05:58.060 --> 05:58.780
To the left.

05:58.780 --> 06:01.090
Don't be that way and show your face.

06:01.090 --> 06:02.620
Why do you hide from people?

06:05.330 --> 06:06.780
As long as you can see me, I'm fine.

06:06.780 --> 06:08.170
I want to seduce my wife first.

06:08.170 --> 06:09.520
Don’t call me your wife often.

06:09.520 --> 06:11.720
So you're my wife now.

06:12.930 --> 06:15.150
Flashlight. To the left.

06:19.560 --> 06:20.580
Take a break.

06:20.890 --> 06:21.880
You said you were hungry.

06:22.070 --> 06:23.260
Let me see what we got.

06:45.580 --> 06:46.740
Well.

06:47.150 --> 06:49.420
The guy who's fixing the car outside.

06:50.820 --> 06:53.720
Who is he? He used our OR just now.

06:55.290 --> 06:58.370
He's a doctor with the Peacemaker.

06:59.690 --> 07:00.620
Really?

07:01.680 --> 07:03.020
With that handsome face?

07:03.810 --> 07:06.470
Is he by any chance Dr. Daniel?

07:07.230 --> 07:08.900
Do you know him?

07:08.900 --> 07:11.520
I was right. I recognized him at first sight.

07:12.020 --> 07:13.730
I should've talked to him.

07:14.070 --> 07:15.390
Who is this groupie?

07:15.390 --> 07:16.900
Call me a fan.

07:17.360 --> 07:20.040
He's not just Albert Schweitzer.

07:20.040 --> 07:21.800
He's like Albert Schweitzer of Bill Gates type.

07:22.380 --> 07:23.860
His father owns

07:23.860 --> 07:25.150
a private equity fund in Canada.

07:25.150 --> 07:26.230
- Really? - Really?

07:26.230 --> 07:27.190
Yes.

07:27.190 --> 07:30.670
He's very famous among NGO workers.

07:31.010 --> 07:32.510
His mother is Korean,

07:32.510 --> 07:34.340
so he's also famous in Korea.

07:34.340 --> 07:35.940
If he's that rich,

07:36.000 --> 07:37.500
why is he working as an NGO worker?

07:37.500 --> 07:38.720
Because he's rich,

07:38.720 --> 07:40.740
he doesn't have to support himself.

07:40.740 --> 07:42.120
He's looking for the meaning of life.

07:44.470 --> 07:45.520
Where is Dr. Kang?

07:45.820 --> 07:46.730
Still at headquarters?

08:10.050 --> 08:11.140
Don't look.

08:18.100 --> 08:20.510
Is there a secluded place around here?

08:23.520 --> 08:25.290
Isn't that a typical male words?

08:28.530 --> 08:32.480
Let's go to a secluded place. How about that?

08:38.850 --> 08:41.760
You did a great job today.

08:51.160 --> 08:52.630
Only hearing you answer

08:53.210 --> 08:55.080
can I wipe away your tears.

08:59.070 --> 09:00.050
Look at me.

09:13.780 --> 09:15.260
Wow!

09:16.140 --> 09:17.880
How shameless it is.

09:19.840 --> 09:22.480
No matter what happened in the ground.

09:23.830 --> 09:25.380
I wanted to make you feel better.

09:26.110 --> 09:30.480
I feel better because of you.

09:39.380 --> 09:44.330
Thank you for coming back.

09:47.010 --> 09:48.630
If you hadn't been here today,

09:48.630 --> 09:52.800
I would've run away.

09:55.140 --> 09:57.160
If you plan to run away, take me with you.

09:57.910 --> 09:58.580
It'd be more fun

09:58.580 --> 10:01.470
to run away as a couple.

10:28.810 --> 10:32.910
Dia… diamonds are stored in a safe place,

10:32.940 --> 10:35.010
But...you know how it is.

10:35.010 --> 10:36.740
Please give me some more time.

10:41.640 --> 10:43.550
It’s not we promised.

10:43.550 --> 10:46.530
It's like a natural disaster.

10:48.210 --> 10:50.140
A natural disaster is one of the busiest time for men like you and I,

10:50.140 --> 10:54.320
second only to war.

10:54.320 --> 10:56.450
You have until tomorrow to bring me the diamonds.

10:56.900 --> 10:59.900
But there are so many eyes watching.

11:08.090 --> 11:11.570
No excuses. Be quick!

11:11.980 --> 11:15.220
Tomorrow before sunset. Got it?

11:21.770 --> 11:22.830
Got it?

11:22.830 --> 11:24.210
Got it! Got it.

11:50.840 --> 11:52.180
Water...

11:55.730 --> 11:57.440
Anyone?

11:59.620 --> 12:01.780
Help!

12:11.280 --> 12:13.460
I don't care. I'll just die.

12:17.280 --> 12:19.300
You sleepyhead!

12:20.630 --> 12:23.600
Put your helmet on.

12:23.600 --> 12:26.250
Don't forget your helmet.

12:27.020 --> 12:30.850
If your skull breaks, you're going to die?

12:32.740 --> 12:35.320
I'm wearing a helmet.

12:37.610 --> 12:41.090
Please come quickly and save me.

13:02.930 --> 13:05.960
What a beautiful sight! You should do it earlier.

13:07.310 --> 13:10.760
Let's dig through to my office.

13:10.760 --> 13:11.950
Okay! Stop!

13:16.240 --> 13:17.830
Stop the digger for now.

13:17.830 --> 13:19.240
From now on,

13:19.240 --> 13:20.620
Alpha Team will resume its search for survivors.

13:21.120 --> 13:22.530
I want the medical team to stand by.

13:22.530 --> 13:23.260
Copy that.

13:23.260 --> 13:25.670
Why? Why resume the search?

13:25.670 --> 13:27.700
We still have three missing people.

13:27.700 --> 13:29.430
Geez. What the heck are you talking about?

13:29.430 --> 13:30.460
Those three missing people

13:30.460 --> 13:32.790
must be dead by now.

13:33.680 --> 13:35.770
That's the doctor's call to make.

13:37.150 --> 13:40.130
Hey! Sergeant! You must be in charge today.

13:40.130 --> 13:40.880
Please leave here.

13:40.880 --> 13:42.780
I'm not leaving. Listen to me!

13:42.780 --> 13:44.220
- Hey! How dare you. - Please out.

13:46.780 --> 13:48.060
Missing people are survivors.

13:48.830 --> 13:50.750
We never give up on survivors.

13:51.570 --> 13:54.190
Let's search for survivors.

13:55.190 --> 13:56.260
Make the impossible...

13:56.260 --> 13:57.060
possible!

14:06.520 --> 14:07.570
This is crazy.

14:18.530 --> 14:19.800
This is the Taebaek Unit rescue team!

14:22.810 --> 14:24.010
Is anyone in there?

14:24.890 --> 14:26.140
If you hear me, knock three times.

14:40.780 --> 14:42.330
Make the impossible possible.

14:43.550 --> 14:45.240
I'll find the survivors.

14:46.420 --> 14:47.490
This is the Taebaek Unit rescue team.

15:35.620 --> 15:37.410
Sir? Are you with the rescue team?

15:38.550 --> 15:39.720
How can I get him out?

15:39.720 --> 15:44.370
Sir! Please help me. Please.

15:44.730 --> 15:46.700
I'm a doctor.

16:04.180 --> 16:06.640
Aftershock! Everyone! Get out!

16:11.860 --> 16:13.660
Are you okay? Are you hurt?

16:14.920 --> 16:19.210
I'm okay. Get me out of here. Quick!

16:19.750 --> 16:20.810
Take my hand!

16:41.110 --> 16:44.990
What are you doing? It's collapsing! Quick!

16:44.990 --> 16:47.340
Sorry. I'm sorry.

16:48.080 --> 16:52.160
Where are you going? Hey! Get me out of here!

17:10.500 --> 17:11.650
Are you okay?

17:13.690 --> 17:16.130
There's someone inside.

17:16.130 --> 17:18.410
Hey! Doc! Are you okay?

17:18.410 --> 17:19.890
Are you okay? Are you hurt?

17:19.890 --> 17:21.520
There's someone inside.

17:21.900 --> 17:23.369
Hurry! It's collapsing.

17:23.369 --> 17:25.599
There's someone inside. He's Korean.

17:31.170 --> 17:32.510
Stay here

17:32.510 --> 17:34.020
and when the tower building shakes

17:34.020 --> 17:36.340
and tilts more than 10 degrees, blow this whistle.

17:36.340 --> 17:37.220
Yes, sir!

17:38.470 --> 17:40.170
Can you stand by in the situation room?

17:40.810 --> 17:41.930
Are you okay?

17:42.420 --> 17:43.650
I'm okay.

17:43.650 --> 17:45.210
If the seismometer goes up over five degrees,

17:45.210 --> 17:46.490
or if you hear him whistle...

17:46.490 --> 17:47.910
Okay. I get it.

17:47.910 --> 17:49.120
Give me your hand.

17:53.240 --> 17:55.300
You're far from okay.

17:55.300 --> 17:57.420
I'll wrap a bandage around your hand.

18:26.730 --> 18:28.750
Where am I now?

18:31.130 --> 18:32.600
Third floor in the basement?

18:35.050 --> 18:36.060
This is crazy!

18:37.850 --> 18:39.120
Help!

18:40.720 --> 18:42.600
Please get me out of here!

18:47.680 --> 18:49.060
Can you hear me?

18:50.140 --> 18:51.590
Hey!

18:51.590 --> 18:52.860
Can you hear me?

18:52.860 --> 18:54.220
Yes, I can hear you.

18:54.270 --> 18:55.340
Loud and clear.

18:56.610 --> 18:58.270
Can you please help me?

19:04.310 --> 19:05.120
Where is this man?

19:05.120 --> 19:06.290
Third floor basement on the west side.

19:06.290 --> 19:08.540
Alpha Team is securing a path.

19:08.540 --> 19:10.130
Tell him that I'm coming in.

19:14.550 --> 19:15.380
I'll join you.

19:17.270 --> 19:18.530
Prepare a medical kit for me.

19:19.560 --> 19:20.820
You can stand by here.

19:21.170 --> 19:22.320
I need to see the patient.

19:22.320 --> 19:23.640
The first rule of the rescue guidelines

19:23.640 --> 19:25.180
is to not create more casualties.

19:25.920 --> 19:27.540
Until we secure a safe space,

19:27.540 --> 19:28.850
rescue workers

19:28.850 --> 19:30.060
will treat the patient.

19:30.970 --> 19:31.940
Fine.

19:32.170 --> 19:34.800
This is Wolf. Do you copy, situation room?

19:34.800 --> 19:36.650
I can secure the patient in five minutes.

19:36.980 --> 19:38.030
Bring a medical kit down.

19:38.030 --> 19:39.630
Copy that. I'm coming down now.

19:49.980 --> 19:51.290
What are you doing?

19:52.610 --> 19:54.360
You don't think I can read it?

19:54.690 --> 19:56.090
I want to make sure.

19:58.850 --> 19:59.930
I was the top student

19:59.930 --> 20:01.110
in the Army Academy

20:01.110 --> 20:02.510
and at West Point,

20:02.510 --> 20:05.380
where they speak English...

20:05.380 --> 20:07.100
Let me know

20:07.100 --> 20:08.340
as soon as you check the patient's vital signs.

20:11.730 --> 20:12.510
Here.

20:14.890 --> 20:17.430
I'll show you how fluently I can speak English.

20:18.730 --> 20:19.680
Just wait and see.

20:35.110 --> 20:37.960
Did you bring something to eat?

20:37.960 --> 20:40.070
This man gave me only water.

20:40.380 --> 20:41.620
He said I shouldn't eat anything.

20:44.400 --> 20:46.270
He's got no food.

20:46.270 --> 20:48.510
He's quite healthy, but so talkative.

20:48.510 --> 20:49.820
The problem is over there.

20:50.390 --> 20:52.930
We need to secure some space between the two frames with a hydraulic pump.

20:52.930 --> 20:54.980
It's too narrow and it might take some time.

20:55.340 --> 20:56.630
By the way, how did you get here?

20:57.840 --> 20:59.660
You were working on the east side,

20:59.980 --> 21:01.270
so how did you end up on the west side?

21:02.090 --> 21:03.390
Am I on the west side?

21:04.810 --> 21:06.990
I saw a hole and kept crawling.

21:08.660 --> 21:11.520
I should've gone up instead of crawling to the side.

21:13.050 --> 21:14.250
Anyway, get me out of here.

21:14.250 --> 21:17.450
I'm hungry and hurt.

21:17.450 --> 21:18.670
Where does it hurt the most?

21:19.320 --> 21:22.750
BP is 130 over 110 and pulse is 85.

21:22.750 --> 21:25.160
He sprained his left ankle and fractured his right shoulder.

21:25.160 --> 21:26.430
His vitals seem to be fine.

21:26.430 --> 21:27.610
We need to give him

21:27.610 --> 21:29.250
glucose and painkillers via IV.

21:29.660 --> 21:32.640
Do you think you can put him on an IV?

21:32.640 --> 21:33.540
Yes, I can.

21:34.560 --> 21:35.890
Have you done it before?

21:36.610 --> 21:37.670
We're trained in the army.

21:41.860 --> 21:43.060
Have you done it before?

21:44.750 --> 21:46.250
Why does everybody keep doubting me today?

21:47.910 --> 21:50.300
Which one? In the arm or the forehead?

21:50.570 --> 21:51.570
The forehead will hurt a lot more.

21:53.060 --> 21:54.320
I'll go with the arm.

21:56.100 --> 21:59.660
I'll put him on an IV and inject 30 milligrams of NSAID.

22:04.420 --> 22:07.790
We need another hydraulic pump.

22:09.310 --> 22:10.250
I think so.

22:11.530 --> 22:13.320
We need to go out for another one.

22:13.550 --> 22:17.250
Yes. I think you need to get another one.

22:18.740 --> 22:21.650
I'll stay here. The entrance is too narrow.

22:22.230 --> 22:25.020
You go ahead and get it.

22:28.930 --> 22:30.290
Okay. I'll go.

22:51.480 --> 22:54.350
How long have I been stuck in here?

22:54.350 --> 22:56.210
For three days. n.

22:56.810 --> 22:58.540
Over 50 hours.

23:00.780 --> 23:05.070
Did many people die?

23:12.820 --> 23:13.850
Many died,

23:15.540 --> 23:16.960
but many were saved.

23:19.570 --> 23:20.990
You're saved as well.

23:24.200 --> 23:25.990
We don't know that yet.

23:28.170 --> 23:30.320
Why am I so itchy?

23:36.950 --> 23:38.190
Dr. Kang, can you hear me?

23:41.550 --> 23:43.840
He's having a hard breathing and his BP's dropping.

23:44.700 --> 23:46.170
I checked the medicine before I injected it.

23:46.880 --> 23:48.670
You didn't do anything wrong.

23:49.130 --> 23:50.050
What?

23:50.050 --> 23:51.520
It happens occasionally,

23:51.520 --> 23:53.590
but I think he's allergic to NSAID.

23:53.590 --> 23:56.200
His throat will start swelling soon.

23:57.010 --> 23:57.940
What should I do?

23:57.940 --> 23:59.640
Double the amount of the fluid.

23:59.640 --> 24:01.480
He'll be okay if he takes phenylamine.

24:01.480 --> 24:02.660
Don't worry.

24:03.600 --> 24:06.280
But you didn't take any phenylamine.

24:06.580 --> 24:07.530
What should I do?

24:07.530 --> 24:08.930
Sergeant Seo, are you there?

24:09.230 --> 24:10.150
I’ll get it to you.

24:10.480 --> 24:11.440
I go to find it.

24:17.270 --> 24:18.600
How is it inside?

24:18.600 --> 24:19.650
Not good.

24:20.180 --> 24:21.570
It could collapse at any minute.

24:21.570 --> 24:22.930
Here. Phenylamine.

24:32.550 --> 24:33.990
It's not an aftershock.

24:33.990 --> 24:36.550
What's that noise? Check the power plant!

25:00.040 --> 25:02.410
What's going on? Is it an aftershock?

25:04.630 --> 25:05.640
Situation Room! Situation Room!

25:05.640 --> 25:06.750
What now?

25:06.750 --> 25:09.680
I thought I was saved, but what's this?

25:10.460 --> 25:11.640
Head down.

25:14.940 --> 25:17.490
Shi Jin! Are you okay? Shi Jin!

25:18.740 --> 25:19.790
Respond!

25:20.490 --> 25:23.430
Shi Jin! Shi Jin!

25:27.860 --> 25:28.720
The radio’s off.

25:31.090 --> 25:33.440
Big Boss! Big Boss! Do you copy?

25:34.780 --> 25:37.020
Mr. Jin is digging into the building with a digger.

25:37.020 --> 25:39.670
Jerk! Go bring that scum over here!

25:44.030 --> 25:45.700
Now! Hey! Stop right now!

25:45.930 --> 25:48.430
There are people in the building, you scumbag!

25:57.890 --> 25:59.340
We've detained that jerk.

25:59.740 --> 26:01.590
Keep an eye on him.

26:01.880 --> 26:03.130
If someone dies,

26:03.130 --> 26:05.100
I'm going to break his skull first.

26:05.100 --> 26:07.280
Alpha Team, get your tools and come here!

26:07.320 --> 26:08.320
Now!

26:08.320 --> 26:09.210
Yes, sir!

26:13.800 --> 26:15.750
The foundation is unstable. If it collapses...

26:17.710 --> 26:21.460
I won't be able to stop you, will I?

26:24.420 --> 26:25.470
Ma'am!

26:48.180 --> 26:51.690
Sir! Sir!

26:53.280 --> 26:55.410
Sir! Are you okay?

26:57.940 --> 26:59.210
Sir, you're not dead, are you?

27:01.070 --> 27:02.720
Wake up, sir! Please!

27:06.810 --> 27:08.170
I think he's dead.

27:11.440 --> 27:14.440
Hello? Is anybody there?

27:14.950 --> 27:17.150
A man died.

27:20.670 --> 27:22.990
Don't call me "sir."

27:25.120 --> 27:26.130
Are you okay?

27:26.680 --> 27:29.800
Sir, I thought you were dead.

27:34.710 --> 27:35.900
Don't call me "sir."

27:38.590 --> 27:40.120
Is that really important now?

27:42.850 --> 27:44.480
It's always important.

27:50.260 --> 27:51.760
Are you hurt?

27:54.160 --> 27:56.080
It’s not the time worrying about me.

27:56.850 --> 28:01.050
Look at your arm. You're bleeding.

28:01.930 --> 28:02.760
I guess I am.

28:06.860 --> 28:07.960
Your foot is free now.

28:13.410 --> 28:17.330
Why bother? The entrance is blocked.

28:18.310 --> 28:20.670
We're trapped.

28:25.260 --> 28:28.250
This is Big Boss. Situation Room. Do you copy?

28:30.700 --> 28:33.670
This is Big Boss. Situation Room! Alpha Team!

28:33.670 --> 28:35.920
I thought I was lucky enough to live.

28:36.410 --> 28:39.100
Forget it. I'm going to die here.

28:39.920 --> 28:40.930
Don't worry. We're not going to die.

28:42.190 --> 28:44.110
What are you talking about? We've lost contact.

28:47.750 --> 28:49.030
We're going to get out of here alive.

28:50.230 --> 28:53.060
Isn't your girlfriend waiting for you?

28:53.600 --> 28:55.450
I don't have a girlfriend.

28:57.170 --> 28:58.340
Do you have one?

29:00.860 --> 29:01.930
You heard

29:03.460 --> 29:05.240
the voice of the female doctor, right?

29:07.570 --> 29:09.050
I like her a lot.

29:09.050 --> 29:13.520
But she dumped me three times.

29:14.650 --> 29:15.860
I deserve to die, right?

29:15.860 --> 29:17.920
And you're still alive?

29:18.900 --> 29:20.470
If I were you, I would've killed myself.

29:22.010 --> 29:23.790
I'm capable of doing such a hard thing.

29:26.730 --> 29:29.180
This is the Situation Room. Big Boss, do you copy?

29:30.490 --> 29:31.880
Please come in!

29:35.180 --> 29:36.370
It's so frustrating.

29:39.170 --> 29:41.770
He'll be okay. We'll hear from him.

29:44.430 --> 29:46.080
By the way, what are you doing?

29:50.510 --> 29:52.800
I'm ready to help.

29:52.800 --> 29:53.950
I can’t fall apart.

30:13.730 --> 30:15.100
I hope that you'd be okay.

30:21.630 --> 30:22.670
You too, Captain.

30:26.580 --> 30:29.940
I think she's pretty worried at the moment.

30:30.660 --> 30:31.690
She thinks I'm dead.

30:33.750 --> 30:35.060
"Maybe I should've accepted his heart."

30:35.740 --> 30:40.370
She might think like that.

30:41.850 --> 30:43.140
So are you happy now?

30:45.110 --> 30:49.630
No. I'm worried.

30:54.090 --> 30:55.220
Give me your arm.

31:03.130 --> 31:03.980
What's your name?

31:05.100 --> 31:06.500
Kang Min Jae.

31:06.900 --> 31:07.980
Kang Min Jae.

31:07.980 --> 31:09.370
What are you doing?

31:09.770 --> 31:10.780
In case.

31:11.320 --> 31:14.890
In case? What in case?

31:15.090 --> 31:18.980
In case you get out of here alone.

31:19.960 --> 31:21.850
What are you talking?

31:21.850 --> 31:23.230
We have to get out of here together.

31:25.420 --> 31:26.320
Stop talking.

31:27.750 --> 31:28.820
Your throat has started swelling.

31:29.130 --> 31:30.150
Don't talk and stay still.

31:30.530 --> 31:34.030
Geez. My throat is swollen.

31:35.050 --> 31:37.130
Geez! I'm dying.

31:37.130 --> 31:40.730
You're not dying. Don't you trust me?

31:41.820 --> 31:43.180
Don't I look like a reliable person?

31:43.180 --> 31:44.090
Not really.

31:46.150 --> 31:48.080
It's because you're sick.

31:48.080 --> 31:51.010
Anyway, I trust my partners.

31:51.720 --> 31:53.940
I want you to trust them like I do.

32:14.880 --> 32:15.940
It's him!

32:17.090 --> 32:21.130
If you're alive, respond right away.

32:24.910 --> 32:25.750
See?

32:27.170 --> 32:28.170
Somebody’s helping us.

32:28.170 --> 32:29.450
We have survivors!

32:29.450 --> 32:30.870
Medical Team, stand by!

32:36.500 --> 32:37.430
Are you okay?

32:40.990 --> 32:42.080
What's your name?

32:45.740 --> 32:47.370
I'm alive!

32:53.490 --> 32:54.670
He had a motorcycle accident.

32:55.290 --> 32:56.260
Here's the information.

32:58.140 --> 32:59.080
Who wrote this?

33:00.790 --> 33:02.170
Who wrote this?

33:03.010 --> 33:06.430
The soldier guy who saved me.

33:08.950 --> 33:11.910
It's so good to be alive.

33:12.740 --> 33:15.330
I can see a pretty doctor like you.

33:18.220 --> 33:19.970
I worked so hard to save you.

33:21.200 --> 33:22.350
And you're hitting on a doctor.

33:23.990 --> 33:25.390
Send him to the Medical Zone.

33:49.220 --> 33:50.450
Bring a gurney here.

33:55.580 --> 33:56.390
Is there another one?

33:57.460 --> 34:00.570
Me. I'm a patient.

34:07.400 --> 34:08.679
I'll take care of him.

34:13.330 --> 34:14.360
Don't you remember?

34:14.360 --> 34:15.280
What do you mean?

34:15.280 --> 34:17.580
When you heard that Sergeant Seo was okay,

34:17.580 --> 34:18.639
how did you feel?

34:19.620 --> 34:20.460
Just now

34:20.460 --> 34:22.340
I let him go.

34:22.340 --> 34:23.920
That's why I'm treating you nicer than usual.

34:23.920 --> 34:26.070
Can’t you feel it? Sir!

34:26.980 --> 34:28.690
I'll take care of him.

34:28.690 --> 34:29.440
Why don't you

34:29.440 --> 34:30.489
take care of this wuss here?

34:36.960 --> 34:38.940
It hurts a lot.

34:39.310 --> 34:41.110
I'm badly injured.

34:41.110 --> 34:45.489
Did I say you’re not? I'll go take care of you.

34:46.810 --> 34:48.690
Why don't you let go of my wrist?

34:55.489 --> 34:56.659
Why is she so calm?

35:01.200 --> 35:02.000
Are you okay?

35:03.800 --> 35:05.410
Let go!

35:05.410 --> 35:06.480
What should we do with this jerk?

35:07.250 --> 35:08.420
Let go! Let go of me!

35:10.130 --> 35:11.130
Don't touch me!

35:14.090 --> 35:15.440
I guess everybody's okay.

35:16.880 --> 35:17.870
See?

35:17.870 --> 35:21.150
No one died. Isn't that what matters?

35:21.790 --> 35:22.970
What's your problem? Huh?

35:30.950 --> 35:32.220
Let go!

35:35.510 --> 35:36.420
Blood.

35:44.770 --> 35:45.670
You're so cool!

35:57.070 --> 35:58.000
It stings.

36:04.820 --> 36:06.870
Are you hurting me on purpose?

36:07.650 --> 36:09.850
Are you only good at surgeries? Ouch!

36:14.090 --> 36:15.910
I’ve survived from the danger, but you ignored me.

36:17.450 --> 36:18.510
How heartless!

36:28.130 --> 36:29.470
Is this a joke to you?

36:30.940 --> 36:32.920
You almost died.

36:40.340 --> 36:42.180
I said I was so hurt.

36:44.700 --> 36:46.260
I was so scared

36:47.180 --> 36:48.490
that you might have died.

36:55.780 --> 36:57.350
I went in there because I trusted you. e.

37:00.570 --> 37:02.350
You wouldn't have let me die.

37:02.350 --> 37:06.120
Do you go all the way with everything you do?

37:06.450 --> 37:07.790
I'm a thorough man.

37:08.970 --> 37:11.630
I make sure

37:11.630 --> 37:12.910
I stay alive under all circumstances.

37:18.330 --> 37:20.050
Captain, Commander Park is here.

37:20.050 --> 37:21.740
Now? Where is he?

37:21.740 --> 37:24.720
Lie down. You're a patient. You can't go anywhere.

37:24.720 --> 37:25.780
But he's my commander.

37:26.440 --> 37:28.510
Until the IV's done, you can't move.

37:28.680 --> 37:30.780
If you want to keep doing what you like,

37:30.780 --> 37:32.400
which is risking your life,

37:32.400 --> 37:33.840
don't get up.

37:35.030 --> 37:37.270
Tell Commander Park if he has something to say to the captain,

37:37.270 --> 37:38.950
he should come here.

37:40.660 --> 37:42.560
Should... I tell him?

37:42.560 --> 37:44.170
He might lock me up again.

37:44.210 --> 37:45.250
What?

37:46.980 --> 37:47.880
Sir!

37:47.880 --> 37:49.190
Okay. At ease.

37:51.300 --> 37:52.260
Are you badly injured?

37:52.260 --> 37:52.830
No, sir!

37:52.830 --> 37:54.030
He's badly injured.

37:55.850 --> 37:57.510
I'm sure I'm badly injured.

38:00.490 --> 38:01.990
Haesung Hospital will send a plane

38:01.990 --> 38:04.740
to take their employees to Korea the day after tomorrow.

38:05.290 --> 38:06.540
Make sure

38:06.540 --> 38:08.220
they arrive at the airport by 13:00.

38:08.980 --> 38:11.890
Dr. Kang, let me know the passenger list.

38:12.490 --> 38:13.570
Okay.

38:24.590 --> 38:27.600
Hey, you!

38:28.010 --> 38:29.040
Are you the commander?

38:30.260 --> 38:31.860
Let me talk to you.

38:35.240 --> 38:40.030
Look at this. Do you see this?

38:42.480 --> 38:47.290
You! A soldier

38:47.290 --> 38:49.060
who's getting paid with tax money,

38:49.060 --> 38:50.800
yet you beat up a civilian?

38:51.950 --> 38:54.810
I had my own reasons.

38:54.810 --> 38:56.080
Life goes on, doesn't it?

38:58.560 --> 39:03.120
Hey! You're not going to get away with this.

39:03.120 --> 39:05.530
I'll get a doctor's note and report this to the Ministry of Defense,

39:05.530 --> 39:06.830
the Blue Housethe prosecution,

39:06.830 --> 39:08.470
and the police.

39:09.240 --> 39:11.400
I'm going to make sure

39:11.400 --> 39:14.190
you all are expelled from the army.

39:14.190 --> 39:15.650
Just be ready.

39:16.130 --> 39:18.120
I'm going to sue you all.

39:19.320 --> 39:21.190
Fine. Go ahead and sue us.

39:21.740 --> 39:22.600
Good.

39:23.480 --> 39:24.750
In areas where the army is in control,

39:24.750 --> 39:26.860
especially where we are rescuing civilians,

39:26.860 --> 39:29.480
you almost killed several people with a digger.

39:29.480 --> 39:31.040
Let's see what happens if you go to court.

39:31.490 --> 39:32.750
On top of a civil suit and a criminal case,

39:32.750 --> 39:35.290
you'll be tried in military court

39:35.650 --> 39:37.400
for attempted murder with negligence.

39:37.400 --> 39:39.780
Get some extra copies of the doctor's note.

39:40.840 --> 39:42.110
I'm not a soldier.

39:42.340 --> 39:44.900
You're not? You idiots!

39:44.900 --> 39:48.240
Your paycheck is coming from taxpayers,

39:48.240 --> 39:49.280
yet you couldn't control

39:49.280 --> 39:51.130
a crazy civilian in the operation area?

39:51.130 --> 39:52.840
Pack your kits! Now!

39:53.770 --> 39:54.610
Yes, sir!

39:55.990 --> 39:57.290
100 laps around the drill grounds.

39:58.090 --> 39:59.090
Captain Yoo! You're exempt.

39:59.590 --> 40:01.620
Finish getting your IV.

40:01.620 --> 40:02.720
Yes, sir!

40:02.720 --> 40:05.060
When you're done, 200 laps.

40:08.220 --> 40:10.600
I'll do it with my fellow soldiers!

40:13.770 --> 40:14.850
Form a row!

40:17.570 --> 40:19.840
Let me ask you something.

40:20.570 --> 40:22.400
You two beat up that jerk,

40:22.400 --> 40:23.640
so why am I...

40:25.110 --> 40:26.950
I can't stand it when I'm curious about something.

40:26.950 --> 40:28.390
If my wrist were okay,

40:28.430 --> 40:29.380
I would've...

40:29.380 --> 40:30.110
Hit me?

40:30.110 --> 40:31.900
Hit that scum.

40:32.940 --> 40:34.140
Your timing's not good.

40:34.180 --> 40:35.350
Was that the best you could do?

40:35.350 --> 40:36.210
You could've

40:36.210 --> 40:38.520
completely destroyed him.

40:39.870 --> 40:41.230
My timing's not good.

40:41.380 --> 40:43.400
How many laps so far?

40:43.400 --> 40:44.830
This is the seventh lap.

40:45.210 --> 40:47.270
Wow! 27th lap already?

40:47.270 --> 40:49.320
No! Seventh!

40:49.320 --> 40:50.740
If a guy who graduated from the Army Academy

40:50.740 --> 40:52.780
says it's the 27th, it's the 27th.

40:52.780 --> 40:54.010
Yes, sir!

40:59.780 --> 41:01.370
I have a meeting with my doctor.

41:02.110 --> 41:03.600
I could die while running.

41:08.810 --> 41:09.720
You took the IV out.

41:11.280 --> 41:13.600
I meant it when I said you needed rest.

41:13.940 --> 41:15.200
You shouldn't have come here.

41:16.280 --> 41:18.990
You're the one who's helping me the least when I try to rest.

41:20.290 --> 41:22.090
What have you done wrong this time?

41:23.600 --> 41:24.690
I didn't do anything wrong.

41:25.300 --> 41:27.830
Because it's an order, right?

41:29.790 --> 41:33.110
This is a very unfair and rigid organization.

41:33.110 --> 41:34.870
We stick to the principles.

41:34.870 --> 41:36.460
I don't care about the principles.

41:36.460 --> 41:38.580
I want to see you live.

41:39.780 --> 41:41.470
Take this half an hour after every meal.

41:47.570 --> 41:48.550
Thank you

41:50.260 --> 41:51.220
for saving my life.

41:52.240 --> 41:54.100
I'll give you the list of passengers later.

41:55.810 --> 41:58.140
Do you have the list?

41:58.920 --> 42:00.660
We have a meeting now.

42:03.870 --> 42:06.770
Are you on the list?

42:11.220 --> 42:12.570
Are you?

42:13.100 --> 42:17.180
This is my chance to stand you up.

42:42.360 --> 42:43.500
Is everybody here?

42:44.390 --> 42:45.600
The flight f

42:46.350 --> 42:47.730
or the medical services team

42:47.730 --> 42:50.180
is set to take off the day after tomorrow.

42:51.280 --> 42:53.510
We've completed our term here,

42:53.510 --> 42:55.850
so you can all go home.

42:56.390 --> 42:58.000
Or

42:58.340 --> 42:59.940
you can stay if you want to.

43:01.430 --> 43:03.670
I don't know when the next flight will be

43:04.000 --> 43:06.780
if we miss this one.

43:06.780 --> 43:09.610
Thus far, things have been chaotic,

43:10.340 --> 43:12.740
but you can make a choice now.

43:13.410 --> 43:16.310
Raise your hand if you want to stay.

43:21.370 --> 43:22.840
The concussion patient in bed eight

43:22.840 --> 43:24.360
needs an MRI.

43:24.970 --> 43:26.720
Give him my seat

43:26.720 --> 43:27.870
so he can go back to Korea.

43:30.630 --> 43:34.610
Hey, Ha Ja Ae! What do you think you're doing?

43:35.360 --> 43:38.550
I'm going to give my seat to the patient in bed 10.

43:39.320 --> 43:41.410
I have a patient to check on.

43:42.120 --> 43:43.400
Excuse me.

43:48.530 --> 43:49.550
What's wrong with them?

43:49.980 --> 43:52.810
They're making us look bad.

43:53.760 --> 43:56.670
Dr. Kang, I'm sorry

43:57.410 --> 43:58.550
but I want to go home.

43:58.550 --> 43:59.910
Yes! We have to go.

43:59.910 --> 44:01.180
Let's go.

44:01.930 --> 44:03.890
You don't have to apologize.

44:03.890 --> 44:07.570
That goes for all of you. Don't feel pressured.

44:07.980 --> 44:08.820
You've done more than enough

44:08.820 --> 44:11.130
so far.

44:11.160 --> 44:14.420
If you want to go home,

44:18.920 --> 44:20.450
raise your hand.

44:23.640 --> 44:25.250
Dr. Song, you can go home if you want.

44:25.250 --> 44:28.150
Why are you singling me out? I'm not going!

44:32.620 --> 44:33.960
Leave my seat vacant!

44:35.200 --> 44:36.460
My soul will be sitting in it.

44:43.500 --> 44:47.330
By the way, where's Dr. Lee Chi Hoon?

44:59.060 --> 45:03.580
So itchy. Sand.

45:22.440 --> 45:26.750
You said you are a doctor. But you aren't.

45:26.750 --> 45:29.240
You ran away and left a patient behind.

45:29.660 --> 45:31.000
What kind of doctors you are?

45:42.280 --> 45:43.540
What are you doing?

45:43.950 --> 45:45.360
We had a meeting.

45:47.040 --> 45:48.090
I'm sorry.

45:50.410 --> 45:52.280
I heard you found him first.

45:53.220 --> 45:54.530
You did a good job. me.

45:57.370 --> 45:59.760
Our flight to go home is ready.

46:00.310 --> 46:02.140
Some will stay and some will leave. fair.

46:02.820 --> 46:04.020
I put your name on the passengers' list.

46:04.020 --> 46:05.880
Go home.

46:05.920 --> 46:07.470
Dr. Jang is ready to have the baby.

46:07.470 --> 46:08.740
You have to be with her.

46:10.640 --> 46:11.540
Yes, ma'am.

46:14.890 --> 46:17.960
What's wrong with your hand?

46:23.420 --> 46:24.390
Hey!

46:25.800 --> 46:27.030
Have you seen Mr. Koh?

46:28.420 --> 46:31.980
I had a narrow escape, but where is that old man?

46:32.620 --> 46:34.780
You’re not worried about me at all, huh?

46:36.070 --> 46:37.240
Over there.

46:53.120 --> 46:54.190
Unbelievable!

46:56.530 --> 46:58.340
You said your helmet would save you.

46:59.960 --> 47:02.370
That's why I'm still alive.

47:03.240 --> 47:05.280
I actually listened to you for the first time.

47:07.260 --> 47:09.810
You can't do this to me.

47:09.810 --> 47:13.030
Why?

47:13.030 --> 47:15.980
Why?

47:29.180 --> 47:30.760
Why did you do that?

47:53.450 --> 47:55.110
I'm the captain of the Mouru Unit.

47:55.460 --> 47:56.840
This is today's report on the rescue mission.

47:58.230 --> 48:00.430
One survivor is being treated

48:00.850 --> 48:03.620
and we identified two bodies.

48:04.750 --> 48:08.900
There are no more missing people in the power plant.

48:09.830 --> 48:11.730
As of 11 o'clock today,

48:11.730 --> 48:13.570
we're terminating

48:13.570 --> 48:15.830
the rescue mission on the Mouru Power Plant.

48:17.410 --> 48:18.990
It was an unexpected disaster,

48:18.990 --> 48:21.300
and the Haesung Hospital medical services team

48:21.300 --> 48:23.040
and the soldiers of the Taebaek Unit

48:23.680 --> 48:25.440
worked so hard.

48:25.860 --> 48:27.010
Good work, everyone.

48:27.590 --> 48:34.340
-Thank you. -Thank you.

48:35.000 --> 48:38.390
That means I'm back

48:38.390 --> 48:42.890
in charge of the power plant as of now, right?

48:43.380 --> 48:45.660
Whether I dig a hole or build a castle,

48:45.660 --> 48:47.500
no one should interfere.

48:47.500 --> 48:48.110
I don't care if you're a doctor

48:48.110 --> 48:51.050
or a soldier.

48:54.180 --> 48:55.130
What's that noise?

48:56.880 --> 48:58.520
At this time four days ago,

48:59.810 --> 49:01.460
an earthquake hit us.

49:02.440 --> 49:04.320
As of today,

49:05.270 --> 49:07.630
we'll sound the siren at this hour every day to commemorate the victims.

49:09.170 --> 49:11.160
When you hear the siren, stop what you're doing

49:12.300 --> 49:16.140
and pause for a moment and think about the victims.

49:19.280 --> 49:21.030
Attention!

49:30.100 --> 49:33.720
Bow your heads.

49:54.090 --> 49:56.310
We're rather familiar with death.

49:56.510 --> 49:57.850
We see it a lot at the hospital.

49:58.640 --> 50:01.720
But it was different here.

50:01.720 --> 50:03.830
Physically, you can recuperate

50:03.830 --> 50:06.530
but mentally, it's hard to get over.

50:07.580 --> 50:08.770
After going through this,

50:08.770 --> 50:10.330
I've changed my attitude about life.

50:10.330 --> 50:12.610
I don't know what'll happen.

50:13.830 --> 50:14.870
So,

50:15.870 --> 50:17.240
I'm going to get a new car when I get back.

50:18.150 --> 50:19.470
Which car do you recommend?

50:20.600 --> 50:21.890
Why are you asking me?

50:23.030 --> 50:25.160
Why can’t I ask you?

50:25.160 --> 50:26.880
We've been through a lot together.

50:27.560 --> 50:30.040
Wow.

50:30.650 --> 50:33.460
Marry him! Marry him!

50:33.460 --> 50:34.620
Stop!

50:35.930 --> 50:36.920
The phones are back!

50:38.480 --> 50:39.620
-Geez! -It's working!

50:39.620 --> 50:41.040
It's working!

50:41.040 --> 50:42.520
The communication lines resume.

50:45.540 --> 50:46.720
You’ve already known that.

50:47.780 --> 50:51.050
Even you phones didn’t work, you carry them.

50:52.470 --> 50:53.590
Sir!

50:55.810 --> 50:59.300
I guess my mom's doing just fine.

50:59.760 --> 51:00.780
She's been shopping a lot,

51:00.780 --> 51:02.130
so her legs are fine.

51:02.560 --> 51:04.300
She drank a lot of coffee,

51:04.760 --> 51:06.140
so she's socially active.

51:06.140 --> 51:09.150
Do you know how cool my friends are?

51:09.150 --> 51:12.480
They don't care whether I'm alive or dead. All they want is likes.

51:13.250 --> 51:17.430
My ex is getting married.

51:17.430 --> 51:19.860
How can he send a message like that to...

51:25.010 --> 51:25.810
Yes.

51:27.250 --> 51:30.560
Four of us are staying and we're sending four patients instead.

51:30.560 --> 51:32.320
The director knows

51:32.320 --> 51:33.400
all the patients.

51:33.400 --> 51:35.430
Can you please take good care of them?

51:35.760 --> 51:38.280
Are you worried about the patients?

51:38.280 --> 51:40.640
The plane was for you, you idiot!

51:40.640 --> 51:42.280
Your TV show and

51:42.280 --> 51:43.300
the VIP ward need you.

51:43.300 --> 51:46.090
What about them? Do you want to be Albert Schweitzer?

51:47.060 --> 51:50.050
Right. I'm a sought-after doctor.

51:50.050 --> 51:51.690
Don't try to save mankind

51:51.690 --> 51:53.600
and come back on the next flight.

51:54.010 --> 51:55.230
You're the most important person to me.

51:57.270 --> 51:58.710
Don't worry.

51:58.710 --> 52:00.560
We're over a big hump.

52:01.950 --> 52:04.460
By the way, is Chi Hoon having an affair?

52:04.910 --> 52:06.200
He's not answering his phone,

52:06.200 --> 52:08.080
so Dr. Jang's driving me crazy.

52:52.170 --> 52:54.730
We're in a tough and dry environment,

52:55.700 --> 52:57.680
but look at that gorgeous face.

52:58.810 --> 53:00.920
His existence is a blessing,

53:01.640 --> 53:04.720
but he's good at fixing stuff.

53:13.770 --> 53:15.120
Is it broken?

53:15.120 --> 53:16.130
Yes. Right!

53:18.580 --> 53:21.740
It isn't getting any power.

53:22.440 --> 53:25.130
I heard that you could fix things.

53:25.130 --> 53:26.330
You came the right time.

53:26.330 --> 53:28.760
I can save a person

53:28.760 --> 53:30.510
and fix a machine.

53:30.510 --> 53:34.790
But I can't fix a woman's heart.

53:47.370 --> 53:48.420
What are you doing here?

53:54.630 --> 53:55.850
You should keep your distance with a man.

53:56.350 --> 54:00.600
I don't like this at all.

54:02.180 --> 54:04.630
Not one bit. Dismissed.

54:04.630 --> 54:05.710
Dismissed.

54:08.090 --> 54:09.470
Did you talk to your father?

54:10.480 --> 54:12.860
No news is good news.

54:14.450 --> 54:15.640
What about you?

54:16.480 --> 54:19.330
Lieutenant Yoon is here. You don't have to call her.

54:20.310 --> 54:21.470
You're not wasting any money.

54:22.220 --> 54:23.580
I don't know how long it's been

54:23.880 --> 54:25.310
since we served in the same unit.

54:26.220 --> 54:27.610
I guess we can see each other

54:27.610 --> 54:28.870
when there's an earthquake.

54:28.870 --> 54:32.920
Why don't you just get married?

54:36.040 --> 54:38.270
Shi Jin, the commander wants to

54:38.270 --> 54:40.600
talk to his son-in...

54:52.620 --> 54:53.620
Hey!

54:54.100 --> 54:55.910
Did you just hang up on the commander?

54:55.950 --> 54:57.170
I just hung up on my father.

54:57.170 --> 54:58.530
Son-in-law?

55:01.890 --> 55:03.820
She said Captain. You heard the wrong words.

55:04.450 --> 55:06.140
I thought I could trust you.

55:06.360 --> 55:07.660
Are you two this chummy?

55:08.250 --> 55:09.810
We're not chummy at all.

55:10.580 --> 55:12.370
Don't you think he's jealous?

55:12.370 --> 55:13.560
What’re you talking?

55:16.190 --> 55:18.930
But… She’s the people who made a slip of the tongue.

55:18.930 --> 55:20.380
Why am I in trouble?

55:20.380 --> 55:22.270
You can't say anything to Lieutenant Yoon.

55:24.020 --> 55:25.420
You're such a wuss.

55:25.850 --> 55:28.830
I need to see my doctor.

55:28.830 --> 55:32.400
You broke my heart.

55:49.390 --> 55:50.220
Do you come into his room

55:50.220 --> 55:51.670
like this all the time?

55:51.670 --> 55:54.110
You're jealous.

55:55.340 --> 55:56.150
Keep it up.

55:56.150 --> 55:57.410
What if I am jealous?

55:57.410 --> 55:59.860
I'll reward you. A big one.

56:01.410 --> 56:02.440
You won't be disappointed.

56:06.280 --> 56:07.870
Mic test!

56:07.870 --> 56:10.740
Check! One, two! Check! One, two, three!

56:11.830 --> 56:14.100
Wow! You actually fixed it.

56:14.390 --> 56:15.770
This is how I cure my patients.

56:15.770 --> 56:17.180
Music changes a lot of things.

56:17.670 --> 56:19.730
Can I choose a song?

56:19.730 --> 56:20.820
Sure.

57:13.220 --> 57:17.020
There are just two of us in the room.

57:18.600 --> 57:20.600
And there's music.

57:21.580 --> 57:24.010
Isn't it so romantic?

57:28.380 --> 57:30.410
What are you waiting for?

57:30.790 --> 57:33.100
Don't you think you should do something?

57:33.640 --> 57:34.340
I do.

57:34.340 --> 57:35.500
See?

57:44.500 --> 57:45.870
Go ahead and do it.

57:52.930 --> 57:53.800
It's time

57:53.800 --> 57:55.200
for roll call.

57:56.680 --> 57:57.650
Ma'am.

58:18.170 --> 58:19.450
What's the next song?

58:19.450 --> 58:22.030
I don't know. This is Dr. Kang's list.

58:25.060 --> 58:27.040
If I knew I'd die on foreign soil like this

58:27.040 --> 58:28.080
I would've just enjoyed my life a little more,

58:28.080 --> 58:29.870
instead of competing for the professor position.

58:32.020 --> 58:34.980
Shi Jin, are you on your way?

58:35.500 --> 58:38.070
Why are you not coming?

58:38.570 --> 58:40.760
I’m afraid I can’t wait for you coming.

58:45.630 --> 58:46.880
But

58:47.710 --> 58:48.380
if I die,

58:48.380 --> 58:51.240
I guess you're the first one who'll find me.

58:56.040 --> 59:00.170
You know what? If I'd known I'd die like this,

59:00.580 --> 59:04.200
I would've told you how I felt about you.

59:06.000 --> 59:09.130
A great guy kissed me.

59:10.010 --> 59:12.360
My heart was beating like crazy.

59:41.080 --> 59:43.760
Next Episode

59:43.760 --> 59:46.050
Isn’t it a pity to sleep so early in such a beautiful night?

59:46.050 --> 59:47.050
How about instant noodles?

59:47.050 --> 59:48.130
Did I ask you to do this

59:48.130 --> 59:49.510
every time after a meal?

59:49.510 --> 59:51.250
I wanted to shoot a melodrama with you,

59:51.250 --> 59:52.510
but we ended up in a blockbuster.

59:52.510 --> 59:53.800
Since you destroyed two cars,

59:53.800 --> 59:55.190
why don't I destroy a lipstick?

59:55.190 --> 59:57.340
Are you still happy to see Seo Dae Young?

59:57.340 --> 59:58.130
Yes, sir!

59:58.130 --> 59:59.130
What about you?

59:59.130 --> 01:00:00.460
They kidnap

01:00:00.460 --> 01:00:01.970
and lock people up for human trafficking.

01:00:01.970 --> 01:00:03.460
There's more chance of getting hurt

01:00:03.460 --> 01:00:05.340
being around a guy with a gun.
